          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "### Changing First Name\nUnder certain conditions, Belgian citizens, recognized refugees, or stateless individuals can request a change of their first name. The new name must not cause confusion, harm the individual, or others. The process is initiated at the civil registry of your municipality, and the procedure typically takes up to three months. The cost varies by municipality, with transgender individuals paying a maximum of 10% of the municipal fee."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "### Changing Last Name\nChanging your last name requires a written application to the Name Change Service of the Federal Public Service Justice. Applicants must provide a strong justification and demonstrate serious reasons for the change. The process involves submitting documentation, including a birth certificate, proof of residence, and a criminal record extract. The procedure takes an average of 6 to 12 months."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "### Gender Registration Adjustment\nSince 2018, Belgian law allows transgender individuals to change their gender registration without medical requirements. For minors aged 16 and above, the process requires parental support and a declaration from a pediatric psychiatrist. The procedure includes filing a declaration at the municipal civil registry, followed by a review and legal adjustments. Costs include updating official documents such as ID cards, which typically range between €15 and €25 depending on the municipality."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "### Simplified Surname Change (Starting July 1, 2024)\nFrom July 1, 2024, adults who are Belgian citizens, recognized refugees, or stateless individuals can request a simplified change to their surname. Options include adopting the name of one parent, both parents in a chosen order, or an adoptive parent’s name. The application is processed by the local municipality within one to three months."
